{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf7098080-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5","identifier":"/us/usc/t46/s70505"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"70505"},"text":"§ 70505.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Failure to comply with international law as a defense","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A person charged with violating ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s70503"},"text":"section 70503 of this title","children":[],"tail":", or against whom a civil enforcement proceeding is brought under section 70508, does not have standing to raise a claim of failure to comply with international law as a basis for a defense. A claim of failure to comply with international law in the enforcement of this chapter may be made only by a foreign nation. A failure to comply with international law does not divest a court of jurisdiction and is not a defense to a proceeding under this chapter."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf7098081-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s10/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–304, § 10(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-10-06"},"text":"Oct. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/1688"},"text":"120 Stat. 1688","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/407/tII/s202/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–407, title II, § 202(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/4300"},"text":"122 Stat. 4300","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf7098082-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"i